      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what this 'indemnification' part means. it sounds kinda scary. can u explain it in simple terms?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in simple terms, is basically a promise where one party agrees to cover the costs and losses of another party if a specific bad thing happens. Think of it like this: if you accidentally cause a problem, you agree to pay for the cleanup. It's a way to shift the risk around, making sure one party doesn't get totally stuck with the bill when something goes wrong. It's important, though, so you should always look closely at what exactly you are agreeing to cover.",
