      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "*Gulp.* That sounds like a very serious clause, and you're right to be worried. It means if some other person sues them because they think you stole their copyright, you have to step in and pay for all their legal fees and any damages. It's a heavy burden, but it's a common, albeit sometimes overly aggressive, way to protect the client. It’s a big piece of the contract, so you should definitely have a lawyer look at it before you sign it.",
      "source": "target",
